title: Automated Trap
summary:
thumb|Automated Trap inventory filled with fishes.
Automated Trap is a building part and a deployable technology which can be placed on water and will automatically catch fish over time.
game_description:
An autonomous fishing device, designed for long-term deployment in a wide-range of water conditions.

Once activated, the system will lure and trap any nearby aquatic creatures and store them for later retrieval.
use_info:
thumb|Automated Trap placement blocked by planetary limit.
Automated Trap can be placed on any body of water, and up to three can be placed on each planet. Over time, the four inventory slots will fill up with stacks of fishes that can spawn in the planetary conditions such as weather and water depth do not seem to limit what an Automated Trap can catch, but rarer fishes are less likely to be caught.

title: Exo-Skiff
summary:
thumb|A deployed Exo-Skiff.
Exo-Skiff is an body of water.
game_description:
A deployable static platform, allowing the user to comfortably survey the seas in any weather. As well as providing a steady and easily accessible fishing spot, the Exo-Skiff also features abundant Cold Storage, granting additional space to store your catch.

Summon the Exo-Skiff to any suitable body of water using the Quick Menu (
source_info: This blueprint can be bought from the Exosuit upgrade merchant on the Space Anomaly.
use_info:
thumb|The cold storage inventory screen.
Can be placed from the summon vehicle tab of the Quick Menu.
* Gives the player somewhere to stand over deep water.
* Has two local "Cold Storage" boxes with a shared inventory, which can store any fish or crafted Fishing Bait.
* The colour scheme can be customised.
* The skiff can move - use the summon menu to place it again, as you did when deploying it. It will slowly scoot toward that location instead of teleporting like the Exocraft do. You can even fish while it does so.
additional_info:
* Despite the description, the Exo-Skiff does not protect the player from hazardous weather.
* The platform moves with any waves. The player can be knocked off the skiff in strong storms.

title: Fish
summary: Fish is a category of item that was introduced with the Aquarius Update. 211 different fishes can be caught, not including flotsam.
source_info: Fish can be acquired by fishing, or by using an Automated Trap.
release_history:
*Aquarius - Added as a product.
*Worlds Part II - Added fish found on Oceanic and Gas Giant planets

title: Fish Biscuit
summary: Fish Biscuit is a consumable and one of the Edible Products.
game_description:
A well-baked biscuit, created in the Nutrient Processor. What was once a thin sheet of vaguely-sweetend nutrient paste has been elevated with the addition of carefully chosen ingredients. Flavour profile: fermented, bracing, tangy.
Recipe Complexity: 65%
release_history:
*Omega - Added as a consumable.
*Aquarius - Added a new source and added fishing bait bonuses.

title: Fish Fry
summary: Fish Fry is a consumable and one of the Edible Products.
game_description:
A small morsel of seafood, created in the Nutrient Processor. Food such as this can be highly valuable.

Can be consumed as it stands or subjected to further processing.
use_info: Restores one (1) Core Health square when consumed.

title: Fish Pie
summary: Fish Pie is a consumable and one of the Edible Products.
game_description:
A highly refined food product, created in the Nutrient Processor. It has both the identifying shapes and aromas of an actual food item, in stark contrast with conventional nutrition paste or pellets. Food such as this can be highly valuable. Flavour profile: polyphonic, intense, manifold.
Recipe Complexity: 94%
release_history:
*Beyond - Added as a consumable.
*Aquarius - Added fishing bait bonuses.
additional_info: Grants a 15 second sprint overload once consumed.

summary: The Angler is a fish that can be caught as an item, by the player.
game_description:
Fire dances across the scales of this impossible marine being. Its starlit eyes stare back at you with a meaning far deeper than any fish should know. As they stare, the world around you fades away.

The sound of water fills your ears. It wants to be free. You want to be free...
use_info:
Can be used as water.

Needed to fully complete the Aquarius Expedition.
